product_name: Doggles® ILS Eyewear Dog Goggles
product_description:
product highlights

Doggles ILS goggles are the first and only protective eyewear designed for dogs. Our pups need protection just as humans do, whether it is protection from the sun's harmful rays or protection from wind and debris. Doggles ILS (Interchangeable Lens System) are designed for dogs with a deeper lens cup, wider nose bridge, flexible frame, and soft adjustable head and chin straps. Style may vary.

Features:

  • Vet recommended
  • Polycarbonate (shatterproof), anti-fog, 100% UV protection lenses
  • Elastic adjustable straps - head and chin
  • Foam lined frame for extra comfort
  • Extras deep lens cup keeps the lenses away from eyes
  • Wider nose bridge

    Includes: 1 Pair of Doggles
    Intended Pet(s): Dogs
    Material(s): Rubber frame, Polycarbonate lenses, Elastic Straps
    Color: Black Frame, Blue Lens

    Caution: Never leave your dog unattended while wearing Doggles. This product is intended for use ondogs only. Not for use on humans. Do not over tighten straps.

    Instructions:
    1. Place Doggles on bridge of dog's nose
    2. Place strap imprinted with "Doggles" behind head and under ears
    3. Place bottom strap under chin
    4. Adjust buckles to correct fit

    Doggles have an Interchangeable Lens System (ILS). The lenses are removed by sliding through the top of the frame. To remove, grasp lens and rotate up and out of frame. Be very careful not to damage or remove foam padding.

    To replace lens: Facing the front of the Doggles, the top of the left lens is imprinted with "ILS". Grasp lens, rotate down and click into frame. Be sure there are no gaps between the lens and frame and that the lens is completely in the lens groove. Rotate inward until lens is tight and very secure.

    Product Sizes and Dimensions:
    X-Small (1-10 lb): Head Strap 5 - 13 in, Chin Strap 3 - 7 in; Frame Size 3.5 in; Breed Example: Teacup & Toy sizes Chihuahua, Pomeranian, Yorkie
    Small (9-25 lb): Head Strap 12 - 20 in, Chin Strap 4 - 8 in; Frame Size 4.5 in; Breed Example: Boston Terrier, West Highland White Terrier, Bichon Frise, Cavalier King Charles
    Medium (30-60 lb): Head Strap 15 - 25 in, Chin Strap 5 - 11 in; Frame Size 5.5 in; Breed Example: Australian Shepherd, Border Collie, Brittany Spaniel
    Large (65-100 lb): Head Strap 18 - 30 in, Chin Strap 7 - 16 in; Frame Size 6.5 in; Breed Example: German Shepherd, Labrador Retriever, Boxer
    X-Large (100+ lb): Head Strap 22 - 45 in, Chin Strap 10 - 24 in; Frame Size 7.5 in; Breed Example: Mastiff, St. Bernard, Newfoundland, Great Dane
